snippet.textDisplay:
I use a DeX with my Samsung S10+ regularly at work. I have a Samsung monitor that both my laptop and my DeX connect to along with a a bluetooth mouse and bluetooth keyboard that has three binding options. It makes it nice because I can switch from three different input devices to one monitor.

A smart monitor/laptop would be nice that allows up to three input devices where you can switch between each with a quick key of sorts. Normally I run my primary input in the main display with my phone being displayed in the PIP window. Doing this it can be out of sight but still not miss anything important.

The project I was working on was web-based, necessary tools I was using were web-based, my emails were on my phone anyway, MS Teams and Slack works too and I could just work away all day. Scaling was a bit of an issue so some websites like Confluence and Jira looked a bit scaled up but oh well - could bear with it for a day.

snippet.textDisplay:
What ways do I get for connecting the keyboard and trackpad to something that is not a phone?
I need to sometimes pop into a Mac Mini server sitting in my shelf and sometimes it refuses to stay connected so I need to actually plug a screen in. luna Display might become one option in the future, but this seems pretty legit as an alternative to do so. So, do I just run a USB and HDMI cord over? That would be siiiick.
Using a wireless HDMI transmitter, I could see this also being useful as a secondary display for a desktop setup. This thing is intriguing...
